{"/service/ndnp/pst/batch_pst_holuba_ver02/data/sn83045211/00237280271/1921012101/0809.xml":{"full_text":":2G\nEVENING PUBLIC LEDGERr-PHILADELPHlA, FKID AY, T JANUARY 21, 1921\nJ\nN\nRM\np\nf\nM t!\nI'i\nw\n\nV\nfJ\nvSm\nuu\nmLWrmf\ni\nGrand Trunk Railway\nof Canada\niriiuull\"n National\nllallwajs)\ne-'r Equipment Trust\nGold Certificates,\nSeries F\nlasued nnder toe\n4 Philadelphia I'lan\nTVe offer these Ceriijicatei\ntehen as and 1 timed\nTo Yield About 6.809c\nfelftionlCfy\nComrany\nPhltadalphU 1421 Chestnut St.\nTelephone MOO txxUK\nAtlantic Cltr Chalfonts Dle-ch\n1213 Boardwalk\nPRIC\nE TENDENCIES\nWER\nE\nDOWNWARD\nRiordon Co., Ltd.\nTwenly-Ycar i Bonds\nThese bonds are the obli\ngatVon of one of the largest\nmanufacturers of bleached\nsulphite pulp in the world,\nand can be purchased to\nyield over 8?. Wc recom\nmend the purchase of long\ntime bonds at the present\ntime.\nAsk for Circular F-8\nHarris, Forbes Co.\nIn 6trt, Corner Willis\nNEW YORK\nPHILADELPHIA OFFlCEi\nWidener Bldg.\nOver 8\nStill Obtainable\nAlthough the yield\nof good bonds is\ngradually decreasing\nit is still possible to\ninvest in the more\nconservative type of\nmortgage obligation\nat prices which\nprovide 8o and\nbetter.\nFor an example ask\nfor our Circular\nNo. 7303.\nBonbright Company\n137 Chestnut Street\nPhiladelphia\nNew York Chics, c\nBoston Detroit\nRallies Noticeably Lacked the\nSnap Witnessed in Rocent\nSessions\nNew York, Jnn. 21. Prior tenden\ncies were distinctly downward in to\nday's stock market. This was not be\ncause of nnv adverse developments over\nnight or disturbing news during the day.\nbut entirely the sequence of technical\nInfluences. The stiffening of the call\nmohey rate, however, undoubtedly\ncaused some change in the program\nfor the rise in stocks conducted during\nthe current week by the various pool\ninterests and other speculative combina\ntions. While the declining prices were\ncheeked at different Intervals by Irreg\nular recoveries, the rallies lacked the\nnp witnessed in the preceding sessions,\nand. for the first time In several weeks,\nthe lines of least resistance were on the\ndownward swing of the market pendu\nlum. Call loans opened and renewed over\nthe week at 7 per cent und the supply\nfrom all accounts was not overplrntl\nful. At the same time offerings of time\nwere small. On the other hand, there\nwas continued improvement In the ex\nchange market, with sterling approach\ning its recent maximum figure. The\nmore sensational changes occurred in\nScandinavian bills. Formal announce\nment was made of the closing of the\nnegotiations of the Helglan $30,000,000\n8 per cent loon, although the particu\nlars of the issue were not given. It.\nhowever, had been generally known that\nthe matter was virtually closed, and it\nIs understood is likely to be follow ed by\nother European financing. For the mo\nment these Interesting developments are\nmerely secondary nmrket considerations,\nthe day-to-day movement being more\ninfluenced bj the personality of the\narlous selected demonstrations.\nAs the session progressed, the mnr\nket showed distinct signs of going stale.\nIt likewise reflected the effect of the\nliberal profit -taking of the preceding\nsessions, as well as the abs-ence of the\nsupport of the short interest, which,\nfrom nil indications, has been prac\ntically eliminated. After a lower and\nactive opening, effort wn made to force\na rally under the guiduuee of such\nhighly speculative specialties as Gen\neral Asphalt and Texas Pari lie Coal unit\nOil. The market failed to hold and\nbefore noon the whole list suffered u\nsevere sinking spell, not only canceling\nthe rallies but carying rntes in most\nevery instance under the lower opening\nlevel. A further cut In Pennsylvania\nCrude Oil prices guve a fresh Impetus\nto the downward trend.\nAIMLESS DRIFT\nIN LOCAL STOCKS\nContinued Improvement in\nLiberty and Victory Bonds\nConsidered Significant\nTftrsz\nM\nraj3'j'jxrj\"j\n'JSSFi\nmm\n'jovxrann w\nw\nUOR NEARLY\nI a half century\nCassatt Co. has\nbeen aiding an\never- increasing\nclientele in the\nselection of securi\nties for the profit\nable investment of\ntheir funds.\nThe advantages of\nthis experience are\nyours to com\nrtiarid. CASSATT vV CO.\nCOMMErClAl TRUST BLDG.\nPHlLALEtJrilA\n&AiTi Moat prrr soubsm sen akton\n2\nThe day's dealings In the local mar\nket lacked novelty and initiative. Price\nchanges were unimportant and even\nin the specialties which hnd shown some\ninclination to follow the pool demon\nstrations in the big market the trading\nflattened and assumed much the same\nperfunctory tpe as in the other local\nstocks.\nAlthough the volume of business was\nsmall the trading was well distributed\nand. as a whole, the market continued\nto display good absorption, which was\nmade the more noticeable because of the\nutter absence of anj speculative activi\nties. The brighter side of the day's\nproceedings was again found in the bond\ndivision, especially in thef urllier im\nprovement in the Libert) anil Victorv\nbouds. The gradual enhancement of\nmarket value of these Issues is consid\nered highly significant in the most con\nservative circles, and regarded quite\ngenerallj as foreshadowing milch easier\nmnne market conditions, but which\nlikewise is a precusor of a further slack\neiiing of industrial and buslnes activi\nties. Klectrlc Storage I!atter continued\nthe foremost attraction of the local\ngroup and was run up 1 '-a points to\nHO'tj. although fulr.equentl surrendered\nnrarl) all the gain. Little was done\nir. the Oenerol Asphalt shares. Reflect\ning the thinnes of the current titurket,\nIiutfalo Susquehonna preferred was\nadvanced II points from the previous\nsale to 4. Trading continued light in\nthe utilit group, V. (i. I. was frac\ntionally better. Hoth the Philadelphia\nElectric issues were a shade higher,\nwhile Philadelphia Hnpid Trunsit re\nmained unchanged. Few shares of\nPhiladelphia Traction changed hands at\n.\"ill in the luilrouds Penns; hnnlu,\nufter making a higher start, reacted in\nmpath with the backset in New\nrk. as did Lehigh Valle but Lehigh\nNavigation regained half of jesterday'n\ndecline.\nPhiladelphia Stoclcs\nNEW YORK STOCK EXCHANGE TRANSACTIONS\nSale\n700\n300\n100\n3400\n400\nlion\n35.10\n100\naao\n100\nttoo\n300\n0)0\n100\n890\n10)0\n300\nooo\n1400\n100\n108J0\n.100\n30\ntoo\n3))\n1730\n10)0\n100\nIV)\nA0)\n310\n1100\n3J0\n1000\n3300\n100\n400\n3000\n100\n100\n00\n100\n300\n4400\n300\n13700\n300\n3010\n300\n100\n100\n100\n1(700\n100\n700\n3)0\n000\n100\n300\n300\n300)\n300\n3300\n300\n1000\n100\n4300\n400\n3300\n00\n100\n400\n1300\n100O\n300\ntoo\nton\n100\n3404\ntoo\n310\n300\n700\nf00\n100\n3390\n300\n300\n3R0O\n1300\nB500\n300\n3100\n1400\n100\n100\n400\n1700\n1100\n100\n300\n1700\n1300\n31(04\n300\n800\n1(00\n3390\n100\n400\n100\n00\n300\n300\n300\n100\n1800\n300\n100\n100\n800\n1000\n300\n400\n1000\n300\n3000\nIK. 00\n5100\n300\n3000\n100\n100\n300\n300\nDlv.\nIn\n4\n4\n8\n0\nS\n10\n7\n13\n7\n10\n6\n7\n0\n8\n0\n7\n4\n9\n3\n7\n10\na\n12\n13\n7\n7\n0\n4\n4\ne\n6\na\nio\n7\n7\n7\n10\n10\n4\n10\n4\nl.HO\na\ni\n4\n7\n3\n4\n.SO\n8\n7\n1\nI\nao\nHigh Low\nAjnx Rubber 3M 33\nAlaska Juneau O M.. 1H IK\nAlaska dold Mines... Mi 1ft\nAllied Chom Dye... 33 W\nAllied Chem Dye pf 03 82?.\nAllls-Chalmer 36! 3I.\nAm Agrle Chem 37M 3\nAm Agrle chem pr. 71 7\nAm fieet Sugar 48 47H\nAm Bosch Magneto.. 34 54\nAm Can 38J4 37K\nAm Can pf 87 V, 87W\nAmCar&Fdy 173 133 ft\nAm Car Kdv pf.,.113 113\nAnt Cotton Oil 33 33 H\nAm Drug Syn 7H 1Yi\nAm Kxprcss 133 131\nAm Hide leather. K 9ri\nAm H de Leather pf 48'A tliVi\nAm Ice pf 37& 7&\nAm Internat Corp... 4t 47'A\nAm Unseed fl7'4 8(J\nAm Locomotive 83V& 83\nAm Locomotlvo pf. ..Ill 104\nAm Safety Iloxor.... 8V4 8'4\nAm Ship A Com II UK\nAm Smelt IUsf 31 38l\nAm Smelt A See pf A\nAm Steel Foundries.. 30 Vj 30ft\nAm Sugar Iter 14 03\nAm Sumatra Tob 8 7&\nAm Tel Tel lift llJ\nAm Tobacco Ill 1174\nAm Tobacco B llffij 11H\nAm Woolen (7H Cl'\nAm Woolen 